################################################
PREPARING DESIGN ENVIRONMENT
################################################

Before running Genus or Innovus, prepare the design environment variables.

For example, assume you have the directory:
./data/example

The environment directory consists of:

- floorplan/        (floorplan data for Innovus)
- rtl/              (optional; *.lst is required, another directory may be used)
- sdc/              (constraints)
- mmmc.view         (timing analysis configuration)
- env.sh     (environment setup file)

################################################
GENUS FAST RUN EXAMPLE
################################################

1) Open env.sh and set the following variables:

- ENV_DIR
- ENV_DESIGN
- ENV_LEF_FILES
- ENV_MMMC
- ENV_RTL_LIST
- ENV_INIT_HDL_SEARCH_PATH

2) Open mmmc.view and configure the following sections:

- lib_list_<your corners>
- create_rc_corner
- create_library_set
- create_opcond
- create_timing_condition
- create_delay_corner
- create_constraint_mode
- create_analysis_view
- set_analysis_view

3) Open actual_env.sh and add the following line at the beginning of the file:

source source ./example/env.sh

(the design environment you want to launch)

4) Open a terminal and add the Genus license.

5) Run synthesis:

./run.sh -genus.syn

-- Synthesis has been launched successfully.

################################################
COMMON COMMANDS
################################################

Open terminal and load Cadence tools:

module load cadence/GENUS/21.14
module load cadence/INNOVUS/21.14
module load cadence/CONFRML/22.10.100
module load cadence/MODUS/19.10.000

Run flows:

./run.sh -genus.syn        (simple Genus run)
./run.sh -innovus.fp       (create floorplan)
./run.sh -innovus.impl     (simple Innovus run)


################################################
RUN SUFFIX (OPTIONAL)
################################################

You can add a suffix to distinguish run directories.

Example:

./run.sh -genus.syn -suffix test1